, and of a name spoken in anger and fear: Danka Suth, a Rafter foreman whose hands were everywhere a cable hummed. And there, slick with specks of salt and fungus dust, lay a purse stamped with the eel-skin sigil of the River Lords, an oily boast of coin, power, and the river’s cold current tugging at the city’s ribs. The mission turns on care and witness: follow the Lantern-Queen’s cautious glow, stabilize Kessa’s breath without trading her spine for haste, gather the physical proof that matches the song in the bones, and carry word to the Vigil and Sera Dake before the city’s enemies can choreograph a different ending.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Descend to the Ossuary Gardens using safe ropes and a spore mask, following Thia Mol’s lantern-signal and keeping within sanctioned ladders and anchor points so that no fungal bed is crushed and no taboo rung is taken for speed.\",\n        \"Locate and stabilize Kessa Tharn with calm hands and measured breath; extract her testimony without moving her overly much by cooling her brow, splinting what must be braced, and listening until her story is complete enough to withstand guild knives.\",\n        \"Gather the physical clues that truth can wear in court: the rafter’s knot looped on her wrist, the brine grit wedged in her boot-seams, and the purse stamped with the eel-skin sigil of the River Lords, each bagged and sealed in sight of witnesses.\",\n        \"Secure Kessa’s passage to Vigil care by litter and careful climbers, and alert Sera Dake of the resonant tile diversion at once, invoking the Conclave’s inspection writ to protect the scene and to freeze any attempt to line plates along a forbidden curve.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Sera Dake\", \"lines\": \"Our oath forbids cuts to bone, yet it also bids us lay our palms upon the ribs when they shiver and name aloud the danger in their tremor. Fear sits in my chest like a weight tonight, and it is an honest fear because it 