d pouch you deliver. Sera Dake meets your gaze without flinching and agrees aloud to halt all resonant experiments pending inquiry, which buys you favor with the ordinary craftfolk who fear accidents more than politics. The Rafter Guild roils like a net full of hooked fish, and Gor Relk snarls about theater even as he cannot refuse a joint safety audit under the Vigil’s eye, so Danka Suth slips from his berth and vanishes into a tangle of crew houses. The River Lords send polite denials and angry whisperers, but a dockhand coughs up a ledger fragment that mentions a stamped eel-skin purse, giving you a thin but real thread while also painting a target on your back for those who prefer truths to drown quietly.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C2\", \"title\": \"Move in shadow with the Moth Lanterns and set a sting for Danka Suth\", \"text\": \"I will trust Thia Mol’s small lights and keep my steps on the lattice slats where the fungus remembers not to creak, carrying Kessa’s words instead of Kessa’s weight. We will thread the Undershadows and pass beneath the Crown-Market in the smugglers’ crawl, and there we will whisper a decoy rumor about a cache of resonant tiles being ferried the wrong way up the Chainhouse. I will post two Lantern runners where the catwalks meet the brake drums, and I will take station where I can hear the wind-organ’s smallest change, because sabotage has its own rhythm and I have learned to dance opposite it. When Danka Suth or his knife-hands come to nibble what they think is illicit bait, I will cut their retreat with my hook and let the Lanterns flood them in quiet light while I speak the Hollow Oath to still their more reckless urges. Only after the trap’s jaws have closed will I summon the Vigil, and in that narrow silence between crime and consequence I will ask just one question in a voice that feels like a taut rope: who paid for the eel-skin purse.\", \"outcome\": \"The decoy rumor sparkles through the Undershadows like a thrown coin and land