es water. When he looks past me for help, I will make sure he sees his crews’ faces watching, because a foreman hates disappointing the eyes that trust his knots more than he fears any guild fine.\", \"outcome\": \"The Triad’s platforms shudder to a halt under the Vigil’s temporary sanction, and the echoing clatter dies into a hush that leaves only the drip of cooling lines and the distant five-note sigh of the organ cliffs. Gor Relk bristles like a cat in rain at the interruption, but the writ’s seal and your implacable stance pry a warning concession from him; he allows a walk-through on specific plates while his crews ring the rails and watch. Danka Suth tries three smiles and two alibis, each thinner than the last, and when you set the eel-skin purse between you, his gaze flickers as if a sudden gust pricked his eyes; your oathstone warms enough to sting, and half the watching riggers shift on their feet. He invokes a ‘temporary repair’ and claims the brine is from a night run to Riverfoot, but a younger rigger coughs out that the timing is wrong and that repairs were cut short for a private meeting, which snaps a cable in the room that no hand can re-splice. The Vigil steps in to escort Danka for formal inquiry, Sera Dake orders resonant tiles locked under double seal, and while the River Lords bluster about slander, three toll clerks begin to ask careful questions among themselves, knowing the lesson of wind and web: when one line goes taut, another line reveals who pulled.\"\n      ]},\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M3\"], \"next\": [\"M5\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"Writ\", \"description\": \"Conclave inspection writ bearing Sera Dake’s seal, allowing site access during structural emergencies and granting the authority to halt unsafe work on spans under immediate suspicion.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Consumable\", \"description\": \"A pouch of antibiotic shelf fungus poultice from the Ossuary keepers, enough for several careful 